olive oil
1 packet beef mince
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 sachet beef-style stock powder
1 packet garlic paste
1 tin tomato sugo
1 packet Fresh Fettuccine
1 cucumber
1 bag Mixed Salad Leaves
1 packet Balsamic & Olive Oil Dressing
1 pinch chilli flakes
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese

• Boil the kettle
• Heat olive oil in a frying pan over
high heat
• Cook beef, breaking up with a spoon,
until browned, 4 mins
• Add seasoning, stock, garlic paste,
tomato sugo and a splash of water.
Stir through until heated. Season

• Pour boiling water into a saucepan
over high heat. Return to the boil
• Cook fettuccine in boiling water until
‘al dente’, 3 mins
• Drain, then transfer fettuccine from
saucepan to sauce. Stir through
to coat

• Slice the cucumber
• In a bowl, combine cucumber, mixed
salad leaves and dressing. Season
• Divide beef-tomato sugo fettuccine
between bowls
• Sprinkle with Parmesan and a pinch
of chilli flakes (if using)
• Serve with cucumber salad